[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mQUESTION: "and what was it in 2008?"[0m                                                                                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCONVERSATION HISTORY:[0m                                                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mTurn 1: Q: what was the net favorable prior period development in 2010? | A: -4.6[0m                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mFINANCIAL DOCUMENT:[0m                                                                                                                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mPRE-TEXT:[0m                                                                                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mthe following table shows the impact of catastrophe losses and related reinstatement premiums and the impact of prior period development on our consolidated loss and loss expense [0m  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mratio for the periods indicated. ....[0m                                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mTABLE:[0m                                                                                                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mRow Label       [0m[92m2010    [0m[92m2009    [0m[92m2008[0m                                                                                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mcatastrophe losses and related reinstatement premiums   [0m[92m-3.2    [0m[92m-1.2    [0m[92m-4.7[0m                                                                                                         [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mlarge assumed loss portfolio transfers  [0m[92m-0.3    [0m[92m-0.8    [0m[92m-0.0[0m                                                                                                                         [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mloss and loss expense ratio adjusted    [0m[92m-60.3   [0m[92m-61.7   [0m[92m-62.7[0m                                                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mloss and loss expense ratio as reported [0m[92m-59.2   [0m[92m-58.8   [0m[92m-60.6[0m                                                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mprior period development        [0m[92m-4.6    [0m[92m-4.9    [0m[92m-6.8[0m                                                                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mANALYSIS STRATEGY:[0m                                                                                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't confuse different metrics (net earnings â‰  operating income)[0m                                                                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't ignore conversational context ("that" refers to previous result)[0m                                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't confuse different metrics (net earnings â‰  operating income)[0m                                                                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't ignore conversational context ("that" refers to previous result)[0m                                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mANALYSIS STRATEGY:[0m                                                                                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't confuse different metrics (net earnings â‰  operating income)[0m                                                                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't ignore conversational context ("that" refers to previous result)[0m                                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mANALYSIS STRATEGY:[0m                                                                                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't confuse different metrics (net earnings â‰  operating income)[0m                                                                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't ignore conversational context ("that" refers to previous result)[0m                                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mloss and loss expense ratio adjusted    [0m[92m-60.3   [0m[92m-61.7   [0m[92m-62.7[0m                                                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mloss and loss expense ratio as reported [0m[92m-59.2   [0m[92m-58.8   [0m[92m-60.6[0m                                                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mprior period development        [0m[92m-4.6    [0m[92m-4.9    [0m[92m-6.8[0m                                                                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mANALYSIS STRATEGY:[0m                                                                                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't confuse different metrics (net earnings â‰  operating income)[0m                                                                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't ignore conversational context ("that" refers to previous result)[0m                                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Check if the calculation sequence is logical and appropriate[0m                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Assess if the final result makes business/financial sense[0m                                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ensure proper handling of percentages, ratios, and financial scales[0m                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCommon calculation patterns to verify:[0m                                                                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old Ã— 100%[0m                                                                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Growth rates: (current - previous) / previous[0m                                                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: numerator / denominator[0m                                                                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: value1 - value2[0m                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mProvide your assessment in this format:[0m                                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- APPROVED: If calculation logic is sound and correct[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- NEEDS_IMPROVEMENT: If there are mathematical or logical issues[0m                                                                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mIf NEEDS_IMPROVEMENT, provide specific feedback on what calculations need to be corrected.[0m                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m

[32mâ”‚[0m  [92m1. **Calculation Method**: The method used to calculate the percentage change is incorrect. The expert should have used the formula for percentage change as follows:  [0m              [32mâ”‚[0m
[32mâ”‚[0m  [92m   \[[0m                                                                                                                                                                                [32mâ”‚[0m
[32mâ”‚[0m  [92m   \text{Percentage Change} = \left(\frac{\text{New Value} - \text{Old Value}}{\text{Old Value}}\right) \times 100\%[0m                                                                 [32mâ”‚[0m
[32mâ”‚[0m  [92m   \]  [0m                                                                                                                                                                              [32mâ”‚[0m
[32mâ”‚[0m  [92m   In this case, the "New Value" is -3.2 (2010) and the "Old Value" is -4.7 (2008). [0m                                                                                                 [32mâ”‚[0m
[32mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [32mâ”‚[0m
[32mâ”‚[0m  [92m2. **Mathematical Operations**: The expert's calculation of the percentage change is not performed correctly. The correct calculation should be:  [0m                                   [32mâ”‚[0m
[32mâ”‚[0m  [92m   \[[0m                                                                                                                                                                                [32mâ”‚[0m
[32mâ”‚[0m  [92m   \text{Percentage Change} = \left(\frac{-3.2 - (-4.7)}{-4.7}\right) \times 100\% = \left(\frac{1.5}{-4.7}\right) \times 100\% \approx -31.91\%[0m                                     [32mâ”‚[0m
[32mâ”‚[0m  [92m   \]  [0m                                                                                                                                                                              [32mâ”‚[0m
[32mâ”‚[0m  [92m   This indicates a decrease, which is not reflected in the expert's response.[0m                                                                                                       [32mâ”‚[0m
[32mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [32mâ”‚[0m
[32mâ”‚[0m  [92m3. **Logical Soundness**: The step-by-step reasoning is not logically sound due to the incorrect application of the percentage change formula. [0m                                      [32mâ”‚[0m
[32mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [32mâ”‚[0m
[32mâ”‚[0m  [92m4. **Business Sense**: The final result magnitude does not make sense in the context of financial analysis, as it suggests an increase when the calculation indicates a decrease.[0m    [32mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mANALYSIS STRATEGY:[0m                                                                                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
